{
  "chapter": {
    "id": "web:psalms.55",
    "translationId": "web",
    "bookSlug": "psalms",
    "chapterNumber": 55,
    "referenceLabel": "Psalms 55",
    "summary": "Source text for Psalms 55 in World English Bible."
  },
  "verses": [
    {
      "id": "web:psalms.55.1",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 55,
      "verseNumber": 1,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 55:1",
      "text": "Listen to my prayer, God. Don’t hide yourself from my supplication.",
      "paragraphStart": true
    },
    {
      "id": "web:psalms.55.2",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 55,
      "verseNumber": 2,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 55:2",
      "text": "Attend to me, and answer me. I am restless in my complaint, and moan",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:psalms.55.3",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 55,
      "verseNumber": 3,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 55:3",
      "text": "because of the voice of the enemy, because of the oppression of the wicked. For they bring suffering on me. In anger they hold a grudge against me.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:psalms.55.4",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 55,
      "verseNumber": 4,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 55:4",
      "text": "My heart is severely pained within me. The terrors of death have fallen on me.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:psalms.55.5",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 55,
      "verseNumber": 5,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 55:5",
      "text": "Fearfulness and trembling have come on me. Horror has overwhelmed me.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:psalms.55.6",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 55,
      "verseNumber": 6,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 55:6",
      "text": "I said, “Oh that I had wings like a dove! Then I would fly away, and be at rest.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:psalms.55.7",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 55,
      "verseNumber": 7,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 55:7",
      "text": "Behold, then I would wander far off. I would lodge in the wilderness.” Selah.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:psalms.55.8",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 55,
      "verseNumber": 8,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 55:8",
      "text": "“I would hurry to a shelter from the stormy wind and storm.”",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:psalms.55.9",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 55,
      "verseNumber": 9,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 55:9",
      "text": "Confuse them, Lord, and confound their language, for I have seen violence and strife in the city.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:psalms.55.10",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 55,
      "verseNumber": 10,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 55:10",
      "text": "Day and night they prowl around on its walls. Malice and abuse are also within her.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:psalms.55.11",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 55,
      "verseNumber": 11,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 55:11",
      "text": "Destructive forces are within her. Threats and lies don’t depart from her streets.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:psalms.55.12",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 55,
      "verseNumber": 12,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 55:12",
      "text": "For it was not an enemy who insulted me, then I could have endured it. Neither was it he who hated me who raised himself up against me, then I would have hidden myself from him.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:psalms.55.13",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 55,
      "verseNumber": 13,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 55:13",
      "text": "But it was you, a man like me, my companion, and my familiar friend.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:psalms.55.14",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 55,
      "verseNumber": 14,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 55:14",
      "text": "We took sweet fellowship together. We walked in God’s house with company.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:psalms.55.15",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 55,
      "verseNumber": 15,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 55:15",
      "text": "Let death come suddenly on them. Let them go down alive into Sheol. For wickedness is among them, in their dwelling.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:psalms.55.16",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 55,
      "verseNumber": 16,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 55:16",
      "text": "As for me, I will call on God. Yahweh will save me.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:psalms.55.17",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 55,
      "verseNumber": 17,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 55:17",
      "text": "Evening, morning, and at noon, I will cry out in distress. He will hear my voice.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:psalms.55.18",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 55,
      "verseNumber": 18,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 55:18",
      "text": "He has redeemed my soul in peace from the battle that was against me, although there are many who oppose me.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:psalms.55.19",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 55,
      "verseNumber": 19,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 55:19",
      "text": "God, who is enthroned forever, will hear and answer them. Selah. They never change and don’t fear God.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:psalms.55.20",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 55,
      "verseNumber": 20,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 55:20",
      "text": "He raises his hands against his friends. He has violated his covenant.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:psalms.55.21",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 55,
      "verseNumber": 21,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 55:21",
      "text": "His mouth was smooth as butter, but his heart was war. His words were softer than oil, yet they were drawn swords.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:psalms.55.22",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 55,
      "verseNumber": 22,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 55:22",
      "text": "Cast your burden on Yahweh and he will sustain you. He will never allow the righteous to be moved.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:psalms.55.23",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 55,
      "verseNumber": 23,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 55:23",
      "text": "But you, God, will bring them down into the pit of destruction. Bloodthirsty and deceitful men shall not live out half their days, but I will trust in you.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    }
  ]
}
